(D) Any radio broadcast station, television broadcast 27
station, or cable system participating in the escaped convict 28
alert program or in any local or regional alert program, and any 29
director, officer, employee, or agent of any station or system 30
participating in either type of alert program, shall not be 31
liable to any person for damages for any loss allegedly caused 32
by or resulting from the station's or system's broadcast or 33
cablecast of, or failure to broadcast or cablecast, any 34
information pursuant to the escaped convict alert program or the 35
local or regional alert program. 36
(E) Nothing in this section shall be construed to 37
authorize the use of the federal emergency alert system unless 38
otherwise authorized by federal law. 39

